caption.title: Both induction and inhibition of autophagy increase ZIKV titers in Aag2 cells.
caption.p: Aedes aegypti Aag2 cells were infected with ZIKV followed by chemical treatment (1% DMSO, 1 μM bafilomycin A1, 1 μM torin-1 or 10 μM spautin-1) or treated with dsRNA against Atg5, Atg14, or non-specific control luciferase genes two days prior to infection with ZIKV. Samples were collected for titration 48 hpi. Data was analyzed by one-way ANOVA with a Dunnett’s multiple comparisons test. (*) p<0.05, (**) p<0.01, (***) p<0.001.
